The paper presents algorithms for computing margins of victory in STV elections, which involves techniques from computational social choice, algorithms, and game theory. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves combinatorial optimization and graph theory, which suggests cs.CC (Computational Complexity) as another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper also involves voting theory and mechanism design, which suggests cs.GT (Game Theory) as a possible sub-category.
